observations.recommendation:
3.3 We recommended that the concerned officers strictly comply with the
provision of COA Circular No. 2013-004 on the requirement to
submit list of all on-going government projects/programs/activities
and those that are to be implemented during the year containing the
following information:
a. The project name;
b. Implementing unit, office or division if it is not the agency as a
whole;
c. Brief description of the PPA;
d. Contractor or supplier, if any;
e. Mode of procurement;
f. Funding Source;
g. Cost of approve budget;
h. Project duration including start and completion date; and
j. Location

3.4 We further recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the
MPDO or Municipal Engineering Office to ensure that the
Supervising Auditor (SA) thru the Audit Team Leader (ATL) is
informed within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure
project or before the start of the program/activity that the
appropriate project signboards and or public notices are already
posted.

9.6 We recommended that Management to continue remit all mandatory
contributions/deductions for GSIS/PHIC/Pag-IBIG/BIR within the
prescribed period of remittances to the concerned offices;

3.We recommended that Management:
3.Create an Inventory Committee of at least three (3) or more responsible officials to include always the Property Officer and a representative from Accounting Office;
4.Instruct and supervise the conduct of physical inventory count of all properties of the Municipality with a witness of a representative from the Office of the Auditor;
5.Require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain property ledger cards and reconcile with the report of the Municipal Accountant; and
6.Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) duly signed by the committee members to the Office of the Auditor.

Management:
1.) Strictly comply with the requirements on the submission of all government contracts and all its supporting documents to the Auditor’s Office in accordance with COA Circular No. 2009-001;
2.) the Purchase Orders completely and with relevant information enumerated under Item B of COA Circular No. 96-010 dated August 15, 1996.

Management:
19) Should continue remit all mandatory contributions / deductions for GSIS/PhilHealth within the prescribed period of remittances to the concerned offices;
20) Require all its employees to file their membership to Pag-IBIG;
21) The Municipal Accountant should deduct the mandatory Pag-IBIG contribution and promptly remit monthly contributions together with Agency share to the said Fund.
